#Text=United States : Emergency calls from Great Mills High School shooting released
#Text=Friday , March 30 , 2018

#Text=St. Mary 's County Sheriff 's Office released on Monday audio recordings of calls to the emergency phone line 911 made during the March 20 school shooting at Great Mills High School ( GMHS ) in Maryland , United States .
#Text=The sheriff 's office said the shooter died from a self-inflicted gunshot wound .
#Text=Map highlighting Saint Mary 's County within Maryland .
#Text=Image : Dbenbenn .

#Text=In the shooting incident at GMHS on March 20 , according to St. Mary 's County Sheriff 's Office , Austin Wyatt Rollins , a student at the school , opened fire with a Glock pistol at 7:57AM local time ( 1157 UTC ) ; he shot 16-year-old Jaelynn Willey in the head and also wounded another student , identified as 14-year-old Desmond Barnes , with a single shot .
#Text=Deputy First Class Blaine Gaskill , assigned to the school as a school resource officer , confronted Rollins within three minutes of the first shot .
#Text=Gaskill fired at Rollins , striking his handgun just as Rollins shot himself in the head .
#Text=Rollins died later at hospital .
#Text=In one of the recordings released , Desmond Barnes made a report to the emergency line , " I was just shot in my school . "
#Text=The dispatcher replied , " I 'm sorry ? "
#Text=and Barnes repeated , " I was just shot at my school . "
#Text=The dispatcher then asked , " What school are you at ? "
#Text=and an unidentified female voice interjected , " We 're at Great Mills High School .

column1: #Text=Barnes was released from hospital on March 21 .
#Text=Jaelynn Willey initially survived her head wound .
#Text=However , after two days on life support , her parents held a news conference announcing she was brain dead and they chose to discontinue her life support .
#Text=Willey was declared dead late on the night of March 22 .
#Text=The sheriff 's investigators said Willey and Rollins had been in " a prior relationship which recently ended " and she was not a randomly selected victim .
#Text=Logo .
#Text=Image : March For Our Lives .

#Text=On Saturday , students from GMHS joined a wider demonstration in the United States called the " March for Our Lives " which was primarily inspired by February 's Stoneman Douglas High School shooting in Florida .
#Text=Students , alumni and teachers from GMHS traveled north to Washington , D.C. to be a part of the march .
#Text=Kayla Wells , a senior student , said when speaking to Time magazine , " It should n't happen again .
